def solve(*args, **kwargs):
    s = args[0]
    mp = Counter(map(int, s))
    res = ''
    for ascii_ in range(65, 91):
        (first, last) = divmod(ascii_, 10)
        if first in mp and last in mp:
            if first != last:
                res += chr(ascii_)
            elif first == last and mp[first] > 1:
                res += chr(ascii_)
    return res

def main(*args, **kwargs):
    for _ in range(int(input())):
        arg2 = inp(str)
        res = solve(*(arg2,))
        if type(res) in {list, tuple, set}:
            print(*res, sep=' ')
        else:
            print(res)
main()

T = int(input())
for t in range(T):
    N = str(input())
    val = ord('A')
    ans = ''
    for i in range(26):
        sd = val % 10
        fd = int(val / 10)
        fp = -1
        sp = -1
        fpb = False
        spb = False
        for n in range(len(N)):
            if int(N[n]) == fd:
                fp = n
                fpb = True
                break
        for j in range(len(N)):
            if int(N[j]) == sd:
                if j != n:
                    sp = j
                    spb = True
                    break
        if spb == fpb and spb == True:
            ans = ans + chr(val)
        val = val + 1
    print(ans)
